description: When the alien hero Hyperion was last seen on Earth, the White House was destroyed, the President was killed, and Hyperion disappeared into the stars. Now Joe Ledger, the super-powered government agent Dr. Spectrum, is America's foremost hero. But the source of Joe's power starts driving him lethally out of control...and what happens to Dr. Spectrum - and to our world - when Hyperion comes back?!
name: Supreme Power, Part 2

description: FEAR ITSELF TIE-IN! As armageddon hits the Marvel world in the events of FEAR ITSELF terror grips the planet. An extreme faction of the mutant hate group The Purifiers believes that the end of the world has come, that the devil is here for humanity and it is up to them to "save" as many human souls as they can before he strikes. Can X-Force stop their drive for worldwide suicide? And what, exactly, is a mutant
name: Before the Devil Knows We're Dead

description: On an alien planet, a long time ago, a symbiotic race of bugs have planted themselves in the human race. The bugs make the the humans feel like a drug. The humans infatuated with the extra powers create their entire religion and civilization around these symbiotes.  The narrator Arissa Boddu was playing a fighting game with a brute adversary while her uncle had problems of his own. After receiving an unknown package he runs into the creatures that really control things, the bugs. He teleports himself to his ship having to leave Arissa behind.

The world has plunged into an abyss of terror and despair, and few places are worse right now than in Las Vegas, where the hammer-wielding XXXX XXXXX is passing though -- in his own unstoppable way! Luckily, HARDBALL and his HEAVY HITTERS are here to save the day! Um, right, Hardball and the Heavy Hitters? Right...?
name: Youth In Revolt: Part Three
Paperinik e il nemico numero uno
Paperinik e il club dei bugiardi
Paperinik e il biglietto vincente dei guai

description: When an army of flesh eating Zombies is raised to help in a turf war between two factions of Witches, the other group retaliates by summoning up the baddest demon in hell, Jawbone Grief to do their fighting. But the magic users get more than they bargained for when Grief turns out to an uncontrollable force of nature! Demons, Zombies and mayhem!!
name: The Demon and the Dead

description: When Dr. Dybalacus, Gray Dancer and Pulp kidnap Crunch's reporter friend Boone Philips, it's up to everyone's favorite pint sized powerhouse Crunch Crakerton to save the day!
name: Revenge

description: When universal champion fighter Chapp Dogg comes to Earth looking for challengers, it's up to Crunch to go toe to toe with the hulking alien in a knock down drag out grudge match! Place your bets!
name: Fight

description: In the first chapter of "Universe”: Crunch, Agent Double Danger, Telescopic Man, Battery and Engine Boy travel to another universe to bring down an empirical ruler who has held the galaxy in his iron grip for over a thousand years. Guest starring Bracer and The Free War Messiah. In the second feature "Mechanical Society": Mamma Pain , Telescopic Man and battery must stop the evil robot Dreadgears from taking over the world and finally in "Friendship": Mamma Pain and Telescopic Man battle an army of Ninja's to save an old friend of Mamma Pains from a overly competitive business rival.
name: Hyperactive Comics

description: From famed comics creator Joe Kubert comes this moving coming-of-age story set within Depression-era New York City. Ruby is a handsome young man growing up in a poor Brooklyn Jewish family. When Ruby falls in with a local mobster called Monk, his initial eagerness to make a few dollars to support his hardworking parents ends up getting him in way over his head in the organized crime world. Now he's caught up in both a war between the Jewish and Italian mobs over unionizing factories and an affair with his dangerous mentor's gorgeous moll.
name: OGN

description: These spectacular stories from ACTION COMICS #768, 771, 772 and 773 guest-star the Marvel Family and Nightwing, and include an epic controntation between The Man of Steel and Ra's Al Ghul!
name: 100 Page Spectacular #4

description:
It's chaos in New York when Peter Parker runs across a deadly plan to disrupt a crucial United Nations vote by kidnapping the delegates, and Spider-Man is forced stop the madman with the plan... the leader of Latveria, the man in the iron mask... Dr. Doom himself!

Dr. Doom has taken over the United Nations building, but unknown to him, Peter Parker's school group was taking a tour and is now stuck inside. Doom wants trade concessions for Latveria, or he will explode a zero-gravity bomb.

Pete and Chat break off from their group, and Pete changes into Spider-Man. He recruits a tour guide and some other students to help him. They distract some Doombots while Spidey crawls past them on the ceiling. He makes his way into the main chamber and yaks the bomb's remote away from Doom. Spidey runs out of the building, but tosses the remote into a laundry cart the tour guide is pushing along, so that he can smuggle it out surreptitiously.

Doom follows Spidey, and they go on a chase outside. Doom eventually realizes his mistake and returns to get the remote, but by now they have taken it into laundry truck and are driving away. Doom stops the truck, but the police show up and get ready to arrest him, when another Doom shows up! He says he's the real Doom, and the other one (who took the UN hostage) is just a malfunctioning Doombot. However, a dog that Chat picked up in the UN sniffs him, and tells Chat that the newly arrived Doom is the Doombot--the one who took over the UN is the one that smells human.

The real Doom is arrested (albeit probably temporarily), and Spidey and Chat have once again saved the day.
name: Council of Doom!

description: Corny Rollins, a television science journalist pays with his life for his professional integrity. He's the latest victim, in fact, in a case on which he was investigating, a survey about the death of some children following a severe form of food intolerance. All children also belonged to families that were part of a sample for the detection of the audience index. Nathan and his colleagues continue the investigation from the point where Rollins had broken ...
name: Sesto potere

description:
Branko , May and Andy are on a mission of utmost importance to find out the true origin of the mutates . The group is joined by special agents Mistral and Kay , two mutates that are part of the community of Hell's Island , Shandra , a powerful telepath , and Yoyo, a monstrous mutant child. And while Mr. Alpha and Skotos move in the shadows, Janine finds out that that Andy's health is in bad conditions, and it is getting worse quickly.

The pre-production title of the issue was "L'ultimo dei mutati", but it was finally published as "Il segreto dei mutati". The preview image in the official site of the publisher still has the former title, and shows a cover that actually does not exist...
name: Il segreto dei mutati
The Dog Soldiers: Opening Pandora's Box

description: Returned to earth, the Red Hulk experiences recurring dreams of tragedy. Going to the location of the disaster in his dreams, he encounters M.O.D.O.K and must do battle with M.O.D.O.K's reprogrammed minion, Zzzax.
name: Shock to the System

description: A  girl is found  murdered in her  apartment and  the only clue  from which to draw inspiration for  an investigation  is a  van parked  near their home .  No one can imagine that behind all this  there is  Mister  Alpha and  an experiment  named  Project  Irenaeus .
name: Il dolore della memoria

description: Aristotele Skotos , head of the cult of the Divine Presence , called a council of the major religious sects in the world . In the delegation of representatives of various cults who go on Erato , the space station that will be home to the council, there is also Nathan Never , hired with a personal security task by Joan Rotala , spiritual leader of an important congregation. But the council will be revealed soon be the chessboard on which dark political intrigues weave , warped by the contenders to eliminate uncomfortable opponents.
name: Il Predicatore

description: Cruiserweight wrestler Synn couldn't believe how lucky he was to be recruited by the number one wrestling promotion in North America. Especially when his hero from childhood, the champion Renegade, takes a special interest in him. In time Synn learns he was only brought into the company because Renegade desired him. If he wants to succeed he has to submit to Renegade. If this wasn't bad enough Synn learns little by little that Renegade has a dark past when it comes to his former lovers. Synn walks a tightrope between pursuing his wrestling ambitions, and trying not to become Renegade's next victim.
name: Vol. 1

description: Orchiee Fairchild the third is an exorcist who hops through the land on his pogo stick purging demonic powers with his living marionette companion, Doodoo. Orchiee's travels brings him to Kingsgoie Lanzbarg University where he meets the beautiful student Philip Gillson, who employs him for a spiritual cleansing. A love affair brews between the two right as strange events start happening at the University. A dark force is raping and brainwashing the male students. It's up to Orchiee and Doodoo to put a stop to it. This is an exciting comedy/drama from the creator who brought you the 'Genie's Pawn' story in Kingdom of Selfish Love graphic novel. Also in this book, the new doctor at a French boys' school has his hands full with the beautiful and defiant student Alain. Alain seems only interested in making the handsome young doctor's life miserable, but in time the doctor learns Alain has different motives.
name: Vol. 1

description: The man-slut Orchiee and his marionette side-kick Doodoo are back for another arcane adventure. This time Orchiee gets mixed up with a crooked Colonel who claims his troops needs a skilled exorcist. Turns out he has other motives for luring Orchiee into his army. The creepily kinky Colonel quickly exploits the ranking system once Orchiee is enlisted. He finds himself under the thumb of one real megalomaniac perv! Orchiee may be a nympho, but even he has standards. Meanwhile the Colonel makes sure Doodoo is out of the way by imprisoning him in an army factory that sees nothing wrong with child labor. Doodoo forms a bond with one boy in particular. We gain some insight into the mysterious marionette through the kindness he shows the child. Doodoo flashes back to when Orchiee was a boy, and relives how the unique pair was first brought together. Also in this book: The results of the 'Brainstorm a Yaoi Story' panel we held at Yaoi Con 2005. What happens when a bunch of yaoi fans put their heads together to come up with a manga? This sweet yaoi horror story, that's what!
name: Vol. 2
